Numeric Robustness and Refusal Policy
- Extended envelopes: bilinear, square, chain, log, sigmoid, piecewise; hardened segments (default 10; adaptive 6–12)
- Integer variables enforced across optimize and projection
- Principled refusals on type mismatches and numeric infeasibility; counterexample telemetry exposed
- Convergence labeling: “Convergence (Δμ < ε)” with configurable ε; μ = ρ/(1+χ)

